The Asset Management Corporation of Nigeria (AMCON) has taken over the residence and company of Buba Galadima, a former ally of President Muhammadu Buhari, over debts up to the tune of N900 million. This was disclosed in a statement yesterday by Jude Nwauzor, AMCONs corporate communications head. According to him, Galadima’s Bedko Nigeria Limited owe AMCON nearly N900 million which was purchased during the first phase of Eligible Bank Assets purchase from Unity Bank Plc in 2011. AMCON took over the company on the order of a High Court in Abuja. The order, which was granted to AMCON by Justice A.I. Chikere, the presiding judge gave the Government’s recovery agency the power to take over some properties belonging to the politician. The properties include House No. 15, Addis Ababa Crescent, Wuse Zone 4, Federal Capital Territory (FCT), Abuja and house No. 4, Bangui Street, Wuse 2 also in Abuja. 